In England, in the seven days to 26 November, there were 20,281 new confirmed cases (35.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 November, there were 19,583 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 4% (698 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 01 December is 20,291,473 (35,882.3 cases per 100,000 population).
